content.description:
This is a recent route, not in

Snoqualmie Rock.

Climb a thin face using pocket-like features to a ledge.  Possibly height dependent.

No separate anchor; use the third bolt as a directional for either neighboring anchors.
content.location: Third bolt line from right end, between Pete's Possum Palace (left) and So Funny I Forgot To Rope Up (right)

content.description: Tiptoe up the recently scrubbed slab between Needle Magnet and a large rotten log leaning against the cliff to the left. Nice bubbly features.
content.protection: 2 lead bolts then clip the 3rd bolt on Needle Magnet.  2 new anchor bolts with rings.
content.location: Left of Needle Magnet (the leftmost route on the cliff). To the right of a log leaning up the cliff.

climbs.name: So Funny I Forgot to Rope Up 5.7
climbs.fa: Bryan Burdo, Leland Windham, Sarah Leonard 1999

content.description: Another easy warmup or beginner's lead.
content.protection: 2 bolts, anchor with one chain and one rap ring
content.location: Second route from the far right of gritscone.

climbs.name: So Easy I Forgot to Laugh

content.description: Really easy climb. Quite short, not worth tying in unless your really new or maybe learning to clip.
content.location: Farthest right route. Rap off, walk off to climbers right.

content.description: Easy but fun jug haul with a slight overhang.
content.location: Fourth route from the leftmost route. Left side of the small overhung section.

content.description: Overhanging, pinchy route. Crux is a balance move in the middle of the climb as you stab for a slot and move up to go over a bulge.
content.location: Starts to the left of Girls Best Friend, moves under the left-facing roof.

climbs.name: Pete's Possum Palace
climbs.fa: Bryan Burdo, Leland Windham, Sarah Leonard 1999

content.description: Short easy warmup or beginner's route.
content.location: Fourth route from the right end of Gritscone. On the right side of the big moss patch.

content.description: Short slab climb up a shallow crack.
content.location: To the left of where the Dirty Harry's Peak trail arrives at Gritscone. On the northwest facing side of the wall.

content.description: Currently covered in moss, bring a brush if you want to climb it.
content.protection: 2 bolts + the chains on Needle Magnet.
content.location: 3rd route from the left between Needle Magnet and The Beginning. Rap or walk off to climber's left.

climbs.name: Chica Rapida
climbs.fa: Bryan Burdo, Leland Windham, Sarah Leonard 1999

content.description: Fun face climb. Straightforward climbing on edges till the final moves, a left layback with smooth feet.
content.protection: 4 bolts, anchors up top (walk-off for TR). Anchor is one chain and one rap ring
content.location: This route is in front of the farthest-right tree that's close to the wall. It's the first relatively smooth route after the blocky overhanging section with a Girl's Best Friend and Booty Squirrel.

climbs.name: Booty Squirrel
climbs.fa: Bryan Burdo, Leland Windham, Sarah Leonard 1999

content.description: Crux comes at a small, sharp finger pocket on the left a few moves off the deck. When you hit the pocket keep moving as the holds get better quickly.
content.protection: 4 bolts. Fixed anchors with new chains and lowering biners
content.location: Directly to the left Chica Rapida climbing over a small roof.

climbs.name: The Beginning
climbs.fa: Bryan Burdo, Leland Windham, Sarah Leonard 1999

content.description:
Flakes and a fin on this one.

In the 2018 Snoq. guidebook by Kurt Hicks, this is correctly listed by its original name The Beginning, but over the years folks have mistakenly called it Lucky Arms (e.g., in the photo shown here).
content.location: Start left of Snaffle Baffler, go left of the roof.

climbs.name: A Little Crack Makes Me Laugh
climbs.fa: Bryan Burdo, Leland Windham, Sarah Leonard 1999

content.description: Climb a scrambly set of ledges with a small crack or 2.  Blends into the descent route.
content.protection:
Snoqualmie Rock

says gear to 1.5".  Not sure where anything can be placed.
content.location: Around to the right of So Easy I Forgot to Laugh.  Usually partly buried and/or wet.

content.description: A couple of moves of moderate climbing bring you into a crux reaching for a jug up and left. Finish on more moderate climbing.
content.location: To the left of Booty Squirrel

climbs.name: 99 Grit
climbs.fa: Bryan Burdo, Leland Windham, Sarah Leonard 1999

content.description: Less-than-vertical edging route with an interesting slabby crux at the top.
content.protection: 3 bolts, bolted anchor with one chain and one rap ring.
content.location: In the middle of the wall, to the left of the mossy patch.
